# Loops

There is no traditional for loop in Kotlin unlike Java and other languages.

In Kotlin, for loop is used to iterate through ranges, arrays, maps and so on (anything that provides an iterator).

Kotlin for loop iterates through anything that provides an iterator.

We'll talk about ranges, arrays, maps later in this series, but for now the syntax of for loop in Kotlin is:
```
for (item in collection) {
    // body of loop
}
```

